&lt;li&gt;Lead and/or support benefit audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own open enrollment activities including system testing, communications, and auditing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and maintain standard operating procedures and internal resources to support consistent program administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder &amp;amp; Vendor Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as main point of contact for benefits inquiries to all internal and external stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Legal, Procurement, and HRBPs to address vendor performance, service-level agreements, and pricing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce regular reports and analytics on benefit trends, costs, and utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend enhancements to benefit offerings processes, policies, and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on benefits compliance requirements and market practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
