&lt;h3&gt;Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alarm.com is seeking a DevOps Engineer to help support, automate, and operate the core platforms that power our data and application ecosystem. This role is a hands-on engineering position working across a diverse set of messaging, database, caching, search, and analytics technologies in on-premises, Kubernetes, and cloud environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings a solid base experience in DevOps practices, automation, and production operations, with a focus on reliability, scalability, and continuous improvement. This role will collaborate closely with teams across Software Engineering, Data Engineering, Infrastructure, Cloud Engineering, Security, and Architecture to help deliver stable, well-managed, and highly available services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Support, implement, and help automate enterprise data platforms and messaging infrastructure across hybrid environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Assist in maintaining the reliability, scalability, performance, and operational health of platforms such as Kafka/Confluent, RabbitMQ, Elasticsearch, Snowflake, Redis, MySQL, PostgreSQL, and Microsoft SQL Server.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Contribute to Infrastructure as Code, configuration management, and deployment automation efforts to improve consistency and efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Partner with engineering and infrastructure teams to follow best practices for provisioning, deployment, monitoring, patching, and lifecycle management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Support platform deployments, migrations, upgrades, and maintenance activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Help build and maintain observability capabilities including monitoring, alerting, logging, and telemetry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Troubleshoot production issues, perform root cause analysis, and implement fixes with guidance where needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Contribute to CI/CD pipelines and automation practices that improve release quality and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Maintain technical documentation, runbooks, and operational procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Participate in on-call rotation and incident response efforts to support service reliability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Work with security teams to ensure adherence to standards for access management, encryption, and compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- 2–5 years of experience in DevOps, Site Reliability Engineering, Platform Engineering, or a related technical field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Experience with Kubernetes is a plus, particularly with Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) and deploying or supporting containerized workloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Experience working with one or more enterprise platforms such as Kafka, RabbitMQ, Elasticsearch, Snowflake, Redis, or relational databases (MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQL Server).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Familiarity with cloud and infrastructure environments such as AWS, Azure, or VMware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Experience with Infrastructure as Code tools such as Terraform, Ansible, or similar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Exposure to containerization and orchestration technologies such as Docker and Kubernetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Working knowledge of Linux systems administration; Windows Server experience is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Familiarity with monitoring and observability tools such as Grafana, Prometheus, or similar platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Exposure to CI/CD tools such as GitHub Actions, Jenkins, or similar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Basic scripting or programming skills in Python, Bash, PowerShell, or similar languages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Strong problem-solving skills and ability to collaborate effectively across teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field preferred, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/p&gt;
