&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The International Project Management Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The International Project Management Team is a rapidly growing service offering at Alarm.com. The team provides continuous, high-impact support to international business initiatives, including successful partner service launches, delivery of strategic technical requirements, comprehensive global product deployments, and project management consulting for high-impact initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Project Managers are engaged from early planning through launch and post-launch execution, supporting international business efforts with a disciplined, end-to-end approach across every stage of the project lifecycle. We are building a strong, globally minded team and are looking for exceptional individuals to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Project Managers are responsible for ensuring complex service and product launches meet customer expectations and align with regional market needs and requirements. They coordinate in-region project strategy and execution and lead efforts to resolve complex service, product, and platform release planning challenges that impact business and field operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Project Manager, you will work as part of a driven, collaborative team to apply project management discipline to complex international launches and initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission is to synthesize disconnected inputs - opinions, requests, technical constraints, and business requirements - into cohesive, executable plans that drive successful outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Project Managers are hands-on problem solvers who immerse themselves in our customers’ most intricate business needs and take ownership of executing complex international service and product launches. They actively work through ambiguity and challenges to drive launch success, often operating with a high degree of discipline and grit. At times, Project Managers may be embedded with Alarm.com internal operations and product teams. The role requires curiosity, strong analytical thinking, sound product intuition, a structured and disciplined approach to execution, resilience in the face of obstacles, and a high degree of empathy to drive issues to resolution.&lt;/p&gt;
